    "name": "T-Ritz Saigon Hotel & Apartment",
    "detail": "This is my third time in Vietnam, and Citadines was by far the best hotel for value and experience. I've stayed at far more expensive hotels, but the comfort, style, customer service and amenities are far superior here. The location is great - close to everything, but you're not surrounded by row partying tourists. The rooms were ultra modern, and very well-sized. We got the smallest room size, which was still more than enough space for two people. The gym here is a highlight, with all expensive, brand-new equipment - not just a few treadmills and free weights. There are a variety of machines and ample space for floor work. The staff in particular were wonderful. Amy, the reception manager, was extremely helpful and attentive, going above and beyond to help us with a few tricky requests. She's amazing!! Khong, the gym attendant was also very pleasant - his cheery personality always put us in the best mood. Look no further, this is the best hotel in Ho Chi Minh city!",
